page.title: 01 REVIEW
page.content: The D block which we have named Lickey/Catshill lies 13 miles SW of Birmingham in the extreme NE corner of the County Council of Hereford and Worcester. The town of Bromsgrove is located to the SW. This area divides into roughly two halves. { {1.To the east}are the woods and large country houses of Barnt Green and Lickey and{to the north}the lower slopes of the Lickey Hills where Birmingham city_dwellers still come to find open spaces and fine scenery. {2.To the west and south the largest areas of population comprise the more closely_packed housing of Catshill and Marlbrook with the A38 trunk road to Bromsgrove and the SW and the M5 motorway from junction 4 leading to Droitwich and the SW.
